# Yango Deli — Internal Platform Design Language

Brand-specific design rules for this repo. Combine with the always-on `design-core`
principles and the `ui-design-brain` / `using-ui-stack` skills. Design token source of
truth: `design/tokens/colors.md`, `design/tokens/spacing.md`, `design/tokens/typography.md`.
Full reference: `Yango_Deli_Design_Language_Guide.md`.

## Brand essentials

- **Signature color**: vibrant yellow `#FFCC00` (hover `#E6B800`). Use strategically for
  primary CTAs, active nav/states, and key highlights — never as generic decoration
  (follow 60-30-10: ~60% neutral, ~30% structure, ~10% yellow accent).
- **Yellow always pairs with near-black text/icons** (`#0F1115`) for WCAG AA contrast.
- **Red** only for discounts/urgency/destructive/error. **Blue/purple** as secondary accents.
- **Surfaces**: white cards on light-gray (`#F5F5F7`) backgrounds; subtle token shadow
  (`shadow-sm`), never heavy or per-component novel shadows. No auto gradients.
- **Rounded corners everywhere**: cards `rounded-xl` (12–20px), chips/badges `rounded-full`,
  inputs/buttons `rounded-lg`.
- **Typography**: Inter, strong weight contrast, prominent numbers; `₪` for money.

## Implementation rules

- Use Tailwind spacing on the **8px grid** (`p-2/p-3/p-4/gap-2…`); no ad-hoc pixels.
- Every interactive element implements all 5 states: default, hover, active, **visible
  focus ring** (`focus-visible:ring-2`), disabled.
- Prefer **skeletons** that match the real layout over spinners for loading.
- **Empty states**: short headline + helpful subtext + a primary CTA.
- Badges are **semantic, pill-shaped, limited palette** — no rainbow status colors.
  Recruitment stage colors are defined in `frontend/src/types/recruitment.ts`.

## Trilingual + RTL (non-negotiable)

- All user-facing strings come from i18n (`he` / `en` / `ru`); never hardcode copy.
- Use **logical CSS properties** (`ms-*`, `me-*`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`, `start-*`, `end-*`,
  `text-start`) so Hebrew RTL mirrors correctly. Direction is driven globally by the
  i18n provider (`document.dir`).

## Anti-patterns (do not ship)

- Yellow used for large backgrounds or non-actionable decoration.
- `left/right` utilities in components that must support RTL.
- Color-only state signaling; missing focus states; spinner for predictable layouts.
- New fonts/shadows/radii that diverge from the tokens above.
